@startuml
skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0

class Subject {
    + observerCollection : Collection<Observer>
}

interface Observer <<A>> {
    Notify()
}

Subject "1" *-- "*" Observer

note on link of Subject and Observer 
The diamond indicates aggregation/composition relationship where Subject maintains references to Observers in its collection. The line connects them showing this association exists between these classes/interfaces at runtime through registration mechanisms like RegisterObserver(). This allows dynamic addition/removal without changing core logic - adhering loosely coupled design principles typical for event-driven systems or publish-subscribe patterns commonly seen across various domains including software engineering practices today! 

end note


@enduml
